<h2>About</h2>

<div class="pageGroupBody" id="aboutText">The site features IU address book information, IU Sponsored Research awards, 
Scopus publications, and manually entered course information and pictures. We would like to thank Mark A Price and the 
Digital Library team for data compilation, Chintan Tank and Mike Gallant for installing the VIVO server and interface 
optimization, Nianli Ma for data manipulation and loading, Shanshan Chen and Yuyin Sun for data ontology manipulation 
and mapping and manual data entry. 

<br /><br />

<a href="http://vivoweb.org/">VIVO: A Semantic Approach to Creating a National Network of Researchers</a>, 
is a Semantic Web application and ontology editor originally developed at Cornell University. It integrates research 
and scholarship info from systems of record across institution(s) in support of research discovery and cross-disciplinary 
collaboration. The software can be obtained from <a href="http://www.vivoweb.org/download">http://www.vivoweb.org/download</a>.

